transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, John. My name is Dennis Mann. I placed an order, I think, a day or two ago.

Speaker 1: I'm just following up to see if it got delivered, if it's – when it's the delivery time.

Speaker 2: Yeah. What's your zip code, too, please, sir?

Speaker 1: 14612.

Speaker 2: Thanks.

Speaker 1: 126 Spanish Trail, Apartment F?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. So your order's all set, like it went through. It is going to ship out tomorrow, it looks like.

Speaker 2: So it got approved and then it's set to ship out tomorrow.

Speaker 1: You'll be emailed, your email that we have here, with a tracking link from the Postal Service once it ships.

Speaker 2: Okay. What's usually the time, two days? So what, you think about Monday?

Speaker 1: So you ordered it yesterday. Usually you get it within five to seven days from the day you order it.

Speaker 2: Okay. So probably one day next week. Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah. It'll be sometime next week for sure. It'll probably be around Tuesday, Wednesday.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good one.

Speaker 2: You too.
